4. When to Talk to Each Agent

Project Manager Agent
	‚Ä¢	Planning new work
	‚Ä¢	Reviewing progress
	‚Ä¢	Coordination between agents
	‚Ä¢	Summaries and reporting

Architect Agent
	‚Ä¢	Architecture or folder structure decisions
	‚Ä¢	Repo organization, dependencies, or code standards

Frontend Agent
	‚Ä¢	UI bugs, design tweaks, React component logic

Backend Agent
	‚Ä¢	API routes, Supabase schema, backend logic

Workflow Agent
	‚Ä¢	Automations and Make.com/Activepieces workflows

LLM Trainer Agent
	‚Ä¢	Fine-tuning, model data prep, or prompt optimization

Avatar & Voice Agent
	‚Ä¢	Audio, avatars, and voice integrations

If unsure who to contact ‚Äî always start with the Project Manager Agent.

‚∏ª

5. Logging and Continuity
	‚Ä¢	Every activation or session summary from agents gets pasted into its context file.
	‚Ä¢	The Project Manager Agent merges those logs into 00_MASTER_PROJECT.md.
	‚Ä¢	update_memory.sh and sync_docs_to_github.sh preserve backups automatically.

At the end of each day:
	1.	Check off your Daily Checklist.
	2.	Run both automation scripts.
	3.	Ask the PM Agent to /summarize_session ‚Äî it will output a daily project summary.

‚∏ª

6. Rules of Thumb
	‚Ä¢	Always start with the PM Agent. Keeps the master docs aligned.
	‚Ä¢	Specialists never coordinate directly without PM. Prevents data drift.
	‚Ä¢	After each work session, summarize. Keeps logs consistent.
	‚Ä¢	At the end of the day, run automations. Updates backups and GitHub.
	‚Ä¢	If in doubt, ask the PM Agent. It‚Äôs your control tower.

‚∏ª

7. Daily Loop Summary

Morning:
   ‚Üí Run automations
   ‚Üí PM Agent gives plan

During the day:
   ‚Üí Work with assigned specialist agents
   ‚Üí Test and confirm changes
   ‚Üí Send results back to PM Agent

End of day:
   ‚Üí Run automations again
   ‚Üí PM Agent summarizes progress
   ‚Üí Complete Daily Checklist


‚∏ª

8. In Practice
	‚Ä¢	You manage what gets done.
	‚Ä¢	Project Manager Agent manages who does it and records it.
	‚Ä¢	Specialist Agents handle how it gets done (code, troubleshooting, or design).
	‚Ä¢	Automations keep all files and GitHub perfectly in sync.

